 TANGSHAN, Nov. 27 (Xinhua) -- A cement plant has been renovated and turned into an art zone in Tangshan, N China. Qixin cement plant, founded in 1889, was the first of its kind in China. The plant was removed from its original site in 2008. A museum of cement industry and an art zone were rebuilt there instead. Visitors can learn the history of the plant by looking at the exhibition of tools applied in the cement production. They can also enjoy food and art at studios which were transformed from the workrooms of the plant. The art zone has become a new attraction in Tangshan.  Photo taken on Nov. 25, 2021 shows the night scenery of the Qixin cement plant in Tangshan City, north China's Hebei Province. (Xinhua/Mu Yu)  Aerial photo taken on Nov. 26, 2021 shows the scenery of the Qixin cement plant in Tangshan City, north China's Hebei Province. (Xinhua/Mu Yu)  Visitors enjoy themselves in Qixin cement plant in Tangshan City, north China's Hebei Province, Nov 26, 2021. (Xinhua/Mu Yu)  Aerial photo taken on Nov. 26, 2021 shows the scenery of the Qixin cement plant in Tangshan City, north China's Hebei Province. (Xinhua/Mu Yu)  Produced by Xinhua Global Serviceâ– 